message.content:
cs.DC, cs.SE, cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.OS 

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper investigates the effect of microreboots on end-users of an eBay-like online auction application, which is a distributed system. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is also likely as the paper proposes a new recovery technique for Internet services that requires no changes to the applications or any a priori knowledge of application semantics. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is a possible category as the paper may discuss the security implications of microreboots. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is another possible category as the paper investigates the effect of microreboots on Internet services. 
- cs.OS (Operating Systems) is a less likely category as the paper focuses more on the application-level recovery technique rather than the operating system-level implementation.
